14/12/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- Defence Minister Fatmir Mediu said on Wednesday (December 12th) his country wants to donate excess army ammunition to Iraq and Afghanistan. 
Mediu said he had already tabled the proposal to the United States and other NATO members, adding the project would help Iraq and Afghanistan build their armed forces. 
Albania is presently implementing a programme to destroy its surplus ammunition. 
(Focus - 13/12/07; AP - 12/12/07)
